author: Deb
title: Patrick Nisbett Back In Action In France
text:
October 14, 2015 | 0 Comments 
Bermudian equestrian Patrick Nisbett was back in action taking part in the International Horse Jumping event in France at the Strazeele Horse Grounds. Nisbett competed in both the CSI1* and CSI2* Divisions. 
Nisbett riding Anakta during the CSI1* Grand Prix Selles Equipe 1.35m Table A, One Round with One Jump-off Class finished 7th, the pair recorded a time of 39.49, but they had 8 Penalty Fault Points in the Jump-off. 
During the CSI2* Prix CWD 1.35m First Phase not Table A Against the Clock, but the Second Phase Table A Against the Clock, points of both Phases are Aggregated Class, Nisbett competed on two horses. 
Nisbett and Balasz finished 14th, they clocked a First Phase Clear Round time of 36.58 and then they had a Second Phase Clear Round time of 33.59. Riding Qalva Des Hayettes Z, Nisbett finished 33rd, they clocked a Clear Round time of 35.85 in the First Phase and then they clocked a time of 33.12, but they had 4 Penalty Fault Points in the Second Phase. 
Nisbett and Quick Z finished 19th competing in the CSI2* 1.45m Grand Prix WEO Table A, One Round with One Jump-off Class, they finished 19th clocking a time of 80.44, but they had 5 Penalty Fault Points. Related Stories
